  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The association between cancer and thrombosis is well known and the occurrence of thrombotic
      complications is commonly associated with poor prognosis. The aim os this study is to
      determine the possible value of hypercoagulable parameters as prognostic parameters in
      advanced non-small cell lung carcinoma (NSCLC).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
